    description:
      '906 Rio Vista: Relax is Style in this Upscale Condominium in the Resort Community of Lajitas.\n•\tLuxury Condo with Hot Tub & Views\n•\tGrill, Patio, Propane and Wood Fire Pits\n•\tTwo Bedrooms and Two Full Baths \n•\tViews of Rio Grande, Mountains, Mexico\n•\tWalking Distance to Golf, Spa & DiningThe SpaceLocated in the luxury resort community of Lajitas Texas, 906 Rio Vista is the ultimate home base for your Big Bend vacation. This newly remodeled riverside two-bedroom condo is just a short walk from Black Jack’s Crossing golf course, the Lajitas boardwalk shops, Candelilla Café, Thirsty Goat Saloon, Agave Spa, and the Rio Grande River. The backyard features a large shaded patio and a brand new, four-person hot tub, wood fire pit, propane fire table, comfortable tables and chairs, and breathtaking views of mountains and the Rio Grande River. There are countless reasons to vacation in Lajitas. Come out as soon as you can, but don’t be in a hurry to leave. Once you arrive, you will not want to leave.\n \nThe Rio Grande river basin is directly behind the backyard. The river itself is sometimes in view and sometimes not, depending on the water level and seasonal variations in the riverside vegetation. When the river is high, you can see and hear it. Wildlife, especially birds, that are attracted to the river add to the sights and sounds from the backyard and hot tub. There is also a small pond in front of the property.\n\nPlease Note: At particularly busy times, Lajitas Resort may limit access to the golf course or other resort amenities. We recommend that guests check with Lajitas Resort to verify access to any resort amenities they may plan to utilize. \n\nThe world-famous Black Jack’s Crossing golf course is just half a block from the door. Named after General, "Black Jack" Pershing who pursued Pancho Villa from Texas to Mexico, the golf course is set among scenic mountains and river frontage. Texas Outside ranked it as the "Number One Resort Course in Texas". Golfweek magazine named Black Jack\'s the "Best New Course in Texas." Dallas Morning News described it as the "Best Golf Course You Can Play in Texas". Golf Magazine ranked it the number-one "Most Beautiful Course in Texas". Golfweek listed it as one of the "Best Courses You Can Play in Texas". Bring your clubs and discover what the rave reviews are all about.\n \nOutdoor adventures are virtually limitless. Located between Big Bend National Park and Big Bend Ranch State Park. Scenic drives, hiking, biking, canoeing, rafting, horseback riding, jeep tours, air tours, zip lines, hunting, target shooting, photography, bird watching, star gazing, visiting historic and pre-historic sites, fossil hunting, and much more awaits you with 906 Rio Vista as your home base.\n \nThe house is a two-bedroom, two bath luxury condominium with a comfortable living room, dining area, fully stocked kitchen, laundry room, and an amazing backyard with a shaded porch, fire features, four person hot-tub, and breathtaking views of the Rio Grande, mountains, and into Mexico. Plans have been drawn up for the addition of a viewing deck that extends out over the edge of the Rio Grande river basin. However, don’t worry about construction impacting your stay. No work will be conducted when the property is rented. All work will be completed in phases to make sure no guests are inconvenienced by work in progress.\n \nEnjoy your pick of resort activities, golfing, outdoor activities, or just relax around the house with some Big Bend Coffee Roasters coffee or your favorite beverage.  However active or relaxed you want to be, 906 Rio Vista is the ideal resort rental. Book your stay for as long as possible. Once you arrive, you won’t want to leave. That’s okay, if the dates are available, we will be glad to extend your reservation, or help you book a return trip.InteractionWe manage several properties and live several miles away. We are available by phone, text, email, or messages through Airbnb. We are typically only on site for cleaning or maintenance issues.',
