    description:
      "Casa Mariposa: Live Like a Local at this Restored Rock Ruin in the Historic Terlingua Ghost Town.\n•\tRestored Ruin with Spacious Outdoor Living\n•\tThis is Our Quintessential Ghost Town Rental\n•\tLocated in the Historic Ghost Town\n•\tKitchen, Bedroom and Cozy Room\n•\tFull Indoor Bathroom PLUS a semi-enclosed outdoor showerThe SpaceCasa Mariposa is tucked away on the Ghost Town hillside, surrounded by history. You will be a short trail walk away from all the Ghost Town has to offer: restaurants, art, shopping, and entertainment. This historic miners’ rock house has all the charm Ghost Town living has to offer. Conveniently located between the iconic Big Bend National Park and Big Bend Ranch State Park, Texas’s largest state park.\n \nSpend some time in this restored limestone ruin from the historic Terlingua mining days. Using the original footprint, the house was partly remade in the 1970s. The owners completed an additional restoration in the 1990s and have continued refurbishments recently.\n \nCasa Mariposa is equipped with a full kitchen, two bedrooms, and a full bathroom.  The outdoor living space is spacious and tranquil.  It is perfect for your morning coffee, outdoor dining, relaxing in the shade, admiring Terlingua’s incredible sunrises and sunsets, and star gazing. Relax with a campfire, and soak in the desert peace.\n \nThe 475 square foot interior has a full kitchen, 2 bedrooms, and a full bathroom. You will spend much of your time enjoying the breezy shade of the outdoor living area.  There is a brand new indoor bathroom with hot water, shower, sink, and flushing toilet. Outside, there is also a semi-enclosed bath house has a shower and sink and a quaint outhouse with Chisos Mountain views.\n \nThe Master Bedroom - You’ll find a comfortable queen size bed and plenty of space for all your belongings.  Large windows open out to the patio. Peruse the little collection of books of local interest. The master bedroom has its own entrance and shares a very thick rock wall with the kitchen and the Cozy Room. \n\nIt should be noted that there is not a connecting door between the main bedroom and the rest of the house. Guests need to going outside, on the covered patio, to move from one side of the house to the other. \n \nThe Cozy Bedroom - This simple hideaway behind the kitchen is my favorite room in the house, but it is tiny. The full-size futon just fits in the space.  There is beautiful ceiling of vigas and sotol, a saltillo tile floor, and a little nicho for your knick-knacks.  It maintains the tiny windows that were part of the original design of the miners’ home.\n \nKitchen - The kitchen features handmade cabinets and a handmade table along with stove, fridge, microwave, toaster, and coffee pot. Cookware, spices, etc. are available if you’re in the mood to make your own meals.\n \nPlease note:\nPart of Terlingua Ghost Town’s fun is a bit of funk. It is rugged and remote country.  While most guests prefer the new indoor bathroom, some adventurous travelers prefer to use the original semi-enclose bathhouse or the outhouse.  Because we are located on the hillside, there are multiple levels.  Be prepared to walk up and down short steps and dirt trails.  There’s also a trail through the ruins to the famous Terlingua Porch.\n \nTerlingua is in the Chihuahuan Desert in a remote and rural area. There are no streetlights, and the road to the house is about a half mile of unpaved road. Please drive slowly.\n \nPlease, do not climb on any of the ruins or remove any artifacts.  It is a fragile area.InteractionWe manage several properties and live a few miles away. We are available by phone, text, email, or messages through Airbnb. We are typically only on site for cleaning or maintenance issues.",
