    description:
      "Laughing Horse Retreat: Three Bdrm Home. 217 Acres. Room for 5 or 8 if you add the Guesthouse.\n•\tBring Your Dogs!  \n•\tOne Mile from Christmas Mtns Ranch\n•\t217 Private Acres of Rocky Hills & Valleys\n•\tEasy Access. 9 Miles North of TerlinguaThe SpaceEXTRA FEES MAY APPLY. These might not appear in automated quotes and will be added if applicable.\n     Dog Fees: $150 for one or two dogs. No more than two dogs allowed.\n     Extra Space Cleaning Fee: $85 per stay if the guest house is added.\n     Guest house is required for groups larger than five and optional for any wanting extra space.\n\nLaughing Horse Retreat vacation rental is where y’all want to be. Bring the whole crew and your dogs! Come on out to West Texas for relaxation or adventure. The house sits on 217 acres. Laughing Horse is conveniently located along Texas Highway 118 in the scenic Christmas Mountains, just 10 miles north of historic Terlingua and Study Butte. The main house has a modern kitchen, relaxing porches, three bedrooms with comfortable beds (king, queen, twin)  stunning views, abundant wildlife, desert plants, expansive acreage, and private location combine to provide a truly unique vacation experience.  Add the Guest House for two additional bedrooms and a half bath.\n \nSpend your time around the ranch or enjoying all that the Big Bend has to offer. Then sleep well and wake up relaxed. Go for a hike through the scenic mountains and desert. Walk to our quiet spring and watch the birds. Hang out in the Terlingua Ghost Town. Enjoy the most scenic drives in Texas. Raft down the wild and scenic Rio Grande River. Explore Big Bend National Park. Ride your mountain bike through Big Bend Ranch State Park. Enjoy dinner, drinks and live music in Terlingua. Take a guided jeep tour to some of the area’s most scenic locations. Seek all the adventure you can handle. Or, just sit in a comfy chair on a breezy porch and enjoy the views or a good book. If you don’t have time to do it all, come back again!\n \nLaughing Horse Retreat does not provide horseback riding, rent horses, supply tack, lead trail rides, feed horses, train horses, teach riding, or any other horse related activities.  However, services such as these are available from companies in the area that are not related in any way to Laughing Horse Retreat.NeighborhoodWe manage several properties and live several miles away. We are available by phone, text, email, or messages through Airbnb. We are typically only on site for cleaning or maintenance issues.InteractionWe manage several properties and live few miles away. We are available by phone, text, email, or messages through Airbnb. We are typically only on site for cleaning or maintenance issues.",
