    description:
      "Beautifully renovated, modern and comfortable 27’ 2001 Airstream on 40 private acres. Two air conditioners and heaters, full kitchen, and bathroom. Step outside barefoot onto a 900 square foot composite deck with incredible views of the National Park. Deck includes a large and stylish outdoor kitchen, couch for lounging, and a propane fire table for cool nights. Enjoy our brand new private modern detached bathhouse, with an indoor and outdoor shower. Occupancy limited to 2 adults. No pets.The SpaceWhat you get:\n•\t27' Renovated 2001 Airstream Safari\n•\t40 private acres\n•\t1800 square feet of roof cover (including covered parking area)\n•\t1000 square feet of outdoor living space including kitchen, propane firetable, lounging couch and dining table\n•\t1/2 mile nature trail\n•\tCustom designed and built bathhouse with indoor and outdoor showers that take full advantage of the views and natural light\n•\tLarge scenic overlook (Gazer Point) with excellent access, offering outstanding 360 degree views of the National Park, Mesa De Anguilla, the desert valley, Lajitas Mesa, and beyond.  \n•\tJuiceBox 40 EV Charger for recharging electric vehicles\n\nThe Airstream: The renovated Airstream is equipped with a kitchen (microwave, small oven, small cooktop and sink), two twinXL beds, a small dining table and a comfortable couch.  A smart TV is provided to stream content using your own Netflix/Hulu account (but we recommend spending your time outdoors!).  The Airstream has 2 air conditioners, 2 sources of heat, and offers Wifi (via DSL). Clean, modern and functional, this is the perfect place to lay your head after a day in the park, or riding the nearby bike trails.\n\nThe Deck: Over 1,000 square feet (GIANT) of covered and decked (composite decking) outdoor living space all to yourself. If you’re looking to relax in style, you’re at the right place. Big Bend StarGazer deck offers a large and stylish outdoor kitchen (cooktop/sink/propane grill/dining table/refrigerator) to enjoy meals at home, a couch for lounging, and a propane firetable for those cool nights.\n\nLighting: Dark sky friendly lights in the outdoor kitchen and living areas, red string lights for stargazing, and a BBQ light for grilling after the sun goes down. Our deck railing has very dim LED's mounted underneath to gently illuminate your surroundings.  \n\nThe Bathhouse: Custom designed and built by the owners, this bathhouse is spacious and modern with hot indoor and hot outdoor showers.  The vibrant blue tile vanity wall is reminiscent of the sea that this once was.  The interior is full of light and offers carefully placed windows to enjoy the surrounding views.  The outdoor shower is large, private, and frames the surrounding mountains for viewing while showering.  Hot water, private entry through the bath house, and incredible views make this an experience you won't forget.  \n\nNote: While we are on septic, both of our showers are graywater that is used to feed trees and sometimes the birds will drink this water.  For that reason we ask that you please use the bath products that we supply, so we keep the birds and trees happy and well! \n\nGazer Point: Enjoy your own jaw dropping private scenic overlook with spectacular 360 views of Big Bend National Park and beyond. Outstanding stargazing opportunities from this overlook; one of the best views in the area - all to yourself! You can hike or drive to the turnaround spot.  The overlook is leveled and has large boulders placed for seating; or bring your own chair and experience the view from anywhere.\n\nGazer Trail: Lovely 1/2 mile meandering trail around the property; great for searching for flora and fauna. Fun morning coffee walk, evening margarita walk or just a ‘stretch out your legs’ walk. Gorgeous views and interesting terrain.  Please stick to the trail as much as possible and only take pictures.\n\nLocation: Excellent location and easy access; driveway is located off of paved scenic road FM170, located close to the hustle and bustle but quiet and private.\n•\t2 minutes from the Lajitas Airport mountain bike trails\n•\t6 minutes to BBRSP mountain bike trail head\n•\t12 minutes to the Big Bend National Park entrance.\n•\t11 minutes to Study Butte gas station\n•\t3 minutes to Long Draw pizza\n•\t8 minutes to Lajitas General Store\n•\t5 minutes to Terlingua Ghosttown/Starlight Theatre\n\nSpecial request of our guests: Please visit and enjoy/relax while leaving no trace. Please be conscientious while visiting the fragile desert ecosystem - stay on the trail and limit your water consumption in the shower and at the sink.  StarGazers water supply is rainwater collection and water is very sparse in the desert.  We request keeping showers to 3 minutes.  Please do not remove fossils or rocks from the property - instead take a picture and leave it for the next person to discover.  Thank you for respecting Big Bend and the surrounding desert, treading lightly, and practicing sustainable living during your visit.\n\nOccupancy limited to 2 adults. No pets.NeighborhoodLocation: Excellent location and easy access; driveway is located off of paved scenic road FM170, located close to the hustle and bustle but quiet and private.\n•\t2 minutes from the Lajitas Airport mountain bike trails\n•\t6 minutes to BBRSP mountain bike trail head\n•\t12 minutes to the Big Bend National Park entrance.\n•\t11 minutes to Study Butte gas station\n•\t3 minutes to Long Draw pizza\n•\t8 minutes to Lajitas General Store\n•\t5 minutes to Terlingua Ghosttown/Starlight TheatreInteractionWe manage several properties and live a few miles away. We are available by phone, text, email, or message. We are typically only on site for cleaning or maintenance issues.",
